# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Upshot — .gitignore
# Private, self-hosted personal finance app. Treat all financial
# data and secrets as radioactive: they must NEVER be committed.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Dependencies
node_modules/
.pnpm-store/

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
.next/
out/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# ── Secrets — NEVER commit ──
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
secrets/

# ── Database & financial data — NEVER commit ──
# DB is encrypted at rest, but the file itself + WAL still never belong in git.
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
data/
backups/

# Financial data exports / imports (statements, CSVs, the 2Up source).
# Real data only — sanitized test fixtures live under a fixtures/ path and
# can be force-added if ever needed (git add -f).
*.csv
exports/
*.statement.*
*.pdf
# 2Up source statements + any derived extract (PDF already covered above; this
# also catches non-PDF derivations). Real financial data — never committed.
docs/2up/

# ── V1 reference material (local-only; not part of the V2 codebase) ──
reference/

# ── Master plan stays a local working doc (backups kept elsewhere) ──
# Note: explicit file, NOT a `*.md` rule — design docs/specs (incl. the bundles'
# `Upshot Component Specs.md` and `DESIGN-BRIEF.md`) ARE tracked.
/PLAN-V2.md

# Phase sub-plans stay local working docs too (like PLAN-V2.md).
/docs/superpowers/plans/

# ── Design handoff bundles are tracked deliverables ──
# Re-include their build/ dir (screen sources) which the generic `build/` rule above would otherwise drop.
!design_handoff_upshot/build/

# Testing / tooling output
coverage/
test-results/
playwright-report/
blob-report/
.vitest/

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# Claude / local agent config
.claude/

# Claude Code personal permissions (do not commit)
.claude/settings.local.json

# On-server secrets — NEVER commit
ops/unraid/upshot.env

# Deploy runbook stays a local working doc (contains the owner's real domain).
ops/deploy.md
